        <p>
            Stakx is yet another static website generator just like Jekyll, but it's written in PHP. Now, you're
            probably thinking one of the following things:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>"Why make another static website when Jekyll exists?"</li>
            <li>"But there's already a PHP project called <a href="https://sculpin.io/">Sculpin</a>, why make another?"</li>
            <li>"Ew, why PHP?"</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            I love Jekyll and work with it a lot but Liquid has a lot of short-comings if you're coming from a Twig
            background, like me. Stakx is a proof of concept to build a more powerful static website builder without
            any requirements on superfluous settings, setup, workarounds, etc. Stakx is designed to "just work."
        </p>
